<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Arcgate Walkathon 2026 — Application Flow & Wireframe Blueprint</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333333;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 40px auto;
      padding: 0 20px;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 26px;
      color: #E8622A;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #E8622A;
      padding-bottom: 8px;
      margin-top: 0;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 20px;
      color: #111827;
      margin-top: 30px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;
      padding-bottom: 6px;
    }
    h3 {
      font-size: 16px;
      color: #4B5563;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    p, li {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: #4B5563;
    }
    ul, ol {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      padding-left: 20px;
    }
    li {
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: 20px 0;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    th, td {
      border: 1px solid #D1D5DB;
      padding: 10px 12px;
      text-align: left;
    }
    th {
      background-color: #F3F4F6;
      color: #111827;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    tr:nth-child(even) {
      background-color: #F9FAFB;
    }
    .note-box {
      background-color: #EFF6FF;
      border-left: 4px solid #3B82F6;
      padding: 12px 16px;
      margin: 20px 0;
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    }
    .note-box p {
      margin: 0;
      color: #1E40AF;
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    .footer {
      margin-top: 50px;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 11px;
      color: #9CA3AF;
      border-top: 1px solid #E5E7EB;
      padding-top: 20px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Arcgate Walkathon 2026 — Application Flow &amp; Wireframe</h1>
  <p>This document details the user journey, wireframe mappings, click transitions, and navigation rules from <strong>Login to Logout</strong>. It covers both the 5-Tab Participant view and the 3-Tab Employee view, as well as the active/deleted status of files in the project repository.</p>

  <h2>1. Comprehensive Navigation Flow &amp; Transitions</h2>
  <p>Below is the detailed page-by-page mapping showing exactly which action triggers a change, the target screen, and the method to navigate back.</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Source Screen / Tab</th>
        <th>User Action (Click / Tap)</th>
        <th>Target Destination Screen</th>
        <th>How to Navigate Back / Exit</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Login Screen (Email Step)</strong></td>
        <td>Click "Send Login Code" button</td>
        <td>Transitions to OTP verification step on the same card</td>
        <td>Click "Change email" link (returns to email textbox)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Login Screen (OTP Step)</strong></td>
        <td>Click "Verify &amp; Sign In" button</td>
        <td>Main Dashboard (writes token to localStorage)</td>
        <td>Requires signing out (clears token, returns to Login)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Main App (Any Tab)</strong></td>
        <td>Click Bottom Nav Tab icons</td>
        <td>Switches view to the clicked tab (slide transition)</td>
        <td>Click another Bottom Nav Tab icon</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Dashboard / Profile Tab</strong></td>
        <td>Click on an Activity Card item</td>
        <td>Opens <strong>Activity Detail Modal</strong> overlay</td>
        <td>Click the "Back" button at the top-left of the modal</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Leaderboard Tab</strong></td>
        <td>Click on a participant row or podium avatar</td>
        <td>Opens <strong>Profile Detail Modal</strong> overlay</td>
        <td>Click the "Back" button at the top-left of the modal</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Celebrate Feed Tab</strong></td>
        <td>Click "+ Share something to celebrate" button</td>
        <td>Launches <strong>Post Drawer</strong> overlay</td>
        <td>Click the "✕" close button at the top-right of the drawer</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Celebrate Feed Tab</strong></td>
        <td>Click a post's reaction counter</td>
        <td>Launches <strong>Reactions Detail Modal</strong></td>
        <td>Click the "Back" button at the top-left of the modal</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Activity Detail Modal</strong></td>
        <td>Click the Share icon at the top-right</td>
        <td>Launches <strong>Share Activity Sheet</strong> bottom sheet</td>
        <td>Click "Cancel" button or tap anywhere on the backdrop</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>You / Profile Tab</strong></td>
        <td>Click "Sign Out" button at the bottom</td>
        <td>Login Screen (wipes session state)</td>
        <td>Requires completing the email/OTP verification flow again</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>2. Screen Configurations &amp; Layout Modes</h2>
  <p>The layout adapts dynamically depending on the authenticated employee's role in the walkathon database.</p>

  <h3>2.1 Participant Layout (5 bottom-nav tabs)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dashboard Tab</strong>: Rings progress, current stats, points tally, pace goals, personal bests.</li>
    <li><strong>Leaderboard Tab</strong>: Live rankings by category (Shift/Team), weekly movement indicators.</li>
    <li><strong>Events Tab</strong>: Event calendars, rules, registration drawer.</li>
    <li><strong>Celebrate Tab</strong>: Post sharing and comments feed.</li>
    <li><strong>You Tab</strong>: Multi-panel profiles, Strava connection sync, consistency heatmap calendar, and Sign Out.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.2 Employee / Non-Participant Layout (3 bottom-nav tabs)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Celebrate Tab</strong>: Default active view containing celebration feeds.</li>
    <li><strong>Events Tab</strong>: Lists company active and historical walking events.</li>
    <li><strong>You Tab</strong>: View basic profile details and the Sign Out button. (All Strava integration elements are hidden).</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="note-box">
    <p>Note: The "#recovery-card-wrap" DOM element is hidden from the UI but remains in the HTML as a hook structure. Removing it short-circuits the calculations in "participant-api.js" that display recovery recommendation alerts in the top banner.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>3. Cleaned / Deleted Obsolete Pages</h2>
  <p>To optimize repository weight and prevent build/deployment confusion, the following files were removed from staging:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>app.html</strong>: Old markup tab template. Replaced by <code>participant.html</code>.</li>
    <li><strong>leaderboard.html</strong>: Redundant redirect helper file.</li>
    <li><strong>debug-test.html</strong>: Troubleshooting sandboxed script page.</li>
    <li><strong>ag-config.html</strong>: Obsolete duplicate backup of <code>config.html</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="footer">
    <p>&copy; 2026 Arcgate. All rights reserved. Document created for project reference.</p>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
